Analysis of mouse exp11 16S data

Authored: Kathy N. Lam

Updated: June 27, 2020


Set up

library(tidyverse)
library(scales) #for nice axes
library(phyloseq) #for 16S analyses
library(qiime2R) #for reading qiime objects into R
library(cowplot) #for grid plotting
library(gridExtra) #for coercing upsetr plots into one figure
library(ggpubr) #for grid plotting with common legend
library(phylosmith) #to reorder samples in phyloseq object


Read sample sheet and write metadata

sampledata = readr::read_tsv("sample_sheet.tsv", trim_ws = TRUE)
## Warning: Missing column names filled in: 'X16' [16], 'X17' [17], 'X18' [18],
## 'X19' [19]
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   BioSample_Description = col_character(),
##   Sample_ID = col_character(),
##   Sample_Name = col_character(),
##   Sample_Owner = col_character(),
##   Index_ID = col_character(),
##   Index = col_character(),
##   Index2_ID = col_character(),
##   Index2 = col_character(),
##   Organism = col_character(),
##   Host = col_logical(),
##   Sex = col_logical(),
##   Tissue_Source = col_logical(),
##   Sample_Plate = col_character(),
##   Sample_Well = col_character(),
##   Description = col_character(),
##   X16 = col_logical(),
##   X17 = col_logical(),
##   X18 = col_logical(),
##   X19 = col_character()
## )
sampledata = sampledata %>%
    mutate(Mouse = str_extract(Sample_ID, "M[0-9]+"),
           Timepoint = gsub("_", "", str_extract(Sample_ID, "_[TP].+")),
           Control_Neg = str_extract(Sample_ID, "CTRL_NEG.+"), 
           Control_Std_Human = str_extract(Sample_ID, "CTRL_STD_human.*"), 
           Control_Std_Zymo = str_extract(Sample_ID, "CTRL_STD_Zymo.*"), 
           Control_NTC = str_extract(Sample_ID, "NTC")) %>%
    unite(Specimen, Mouse, Control_Neg, Control_Std_Human, Control_Std_Zymo, Control_NTC, na.rm=TRUE) %>%
    mutate(Sample_Type = Specimen) %>%
    mutate(Sample_Type = gsub("CTRL_NEG.*", "CTRL_NEG", Sample_Type)) %>%
    mutate(Sample_Type = gsub("M[0-9]+", "Mouse", Sample_Type)) %>%
    mutate(Sample_Type = gsub("CTRL_STD_human.*", "CTRL_Human", Sample_Type)) %>%
    mutate(Sample_Type = gsub("CTRL_STD_Zymo.*", "CTRL_Zymo", Sample_Type)) %>%
    mutate(Specimen = gsub("CTRL_STD_human_feces_", "Human ", Specimen)) %>%
    mutate(Specimen = gsub("CTRL_STD_Zymo_DNA", "Zymo DNA ", Specimen)) %>%
    mutate(Specimen = gsub("CTRL_STD_Zymo_mixture_", "Zymo Mix ", Specimen)) %>%
    mutate(Timepoint = gsub("T-2", "Post-Col", Timepoint)) %>%
    mutate(Timepoint = gsub("Pre-Col", "Post-Sm (Pre-Col)", Timepoint)) %>%
    mutate(Mouse = str_extract(Sample_ID, "M[0-9]+")) %>%
    mutate(Day = Timepoint) %>%
    mutate(Day = gsub("Pre-Sm", -5, Day)) %>%
    mutate(Day = gsub("Post-Sm \\(Pre-Col\\)", -4, Day)) %>%
    mutate(Day = gsub("Post-Col", -2, Day)) %>%
    mutate(Day = gsub("T", "", Day)) %>%
    select(-c(BioSample_Description, Sample_Owner, Organism, Host, Sex, Tissue_Source, Description, X16, X17, X18, X19))

readr::write_tsv(sampledata, "sampledata.tsv")

sampledata$Sample_Type = factor(sampledata$Sample_Type, levels=rev(c("Mouse", "CTRL_Human", "CTRL_Zymo", "CTRL_NEG", "NTC")))
sampledata$Timepoint = factor(sampledata$Timepoint, levels=c("Pre-Sm", "Post-Sm (Pre-Col)", "Post-Col", "T0", "T1", "T2", NA))
sampledata$Mouse = factor(sampledata$Mouse, levels=c("M1", "M2", "M3", "M4", "M5", "M6","M7", "M8", "M9","M10", "M11", "M12","M13", "M14", "M15", "M16", "M17", "M18","M19", "M20", "M21","M22", "M23", "M24"))


Examine read count for all samples

fqtools_results = read_tsv("fastq_read_counts.tsv") 
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   Filename = col_character(),
##   Reads = col_double()
## )
fqtools_results = fqtools_results %>%
    mutate(Sample_ID = gsub("data/", "", Filename)) %>%
    mutate(Sample_ID = gsub("_S[0-9]+.*", "", Sample_ID)) %>%
    select(-Filename) %>%
    distinct()

#make new df to manipulate and plot
readcount = fqtools_results %>%
    left_join(sampledata, by="Sample_ID") %>%
    arrange(Sample_Type, Reads)
order=readcount$Sample_ID
readcount$Sample_ID = factor(readcount$Sample_ID, levels=rev(order))

neg=filter(readcount, Sample_Type=="CTRL_NEG")
max = max(neg$Reads)

#also save read counts to metadata to have in phyloseq object
sampledata = sampledata %>% left_join(fqtools_results, by="Sample_ID")
(ggplot(readcount) +
    geom_bar(aes(x=Sample_ID, y=Reads, fill=Sample_Type), stat="identity", width=1, colour="black", size=0.35) +
    scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") +
    geom_hline(yintercept = max, linetype="dashed", colour="black", size=0.5) +
    theme_linedraw(12) +
    scale_y_continuous(name="Reads in fastq file\n", labels=scales::comma, expand=c(0,0)) +
    scale_x_discrete(name="\nSample") +
    theme(panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(), axis.text.x = element_blank(), axis.ticks=element_blank())
)

Convert to phyloseq

po = phyloseq(
  otu_table(svtable$data, taxa_are_rows = T), 
  phy_tree(tree$data), 
  tax_table(as.data.frame(taxtable) %>% select(-Confidence) %>% column_to_rownames("Feature.ID") %>% as.matrix()), 
  sample_data(sampledata %>% as.data.frame() %>% column_to_rownames("Sample_ID"))
  )

po = phylosmith::set_sample_order(po, order)


Filter chloroplast and mitocondria

ntaxa(po)
## [1] 2205
po = phyloseq::subset_taxa(po, (Class!="Chloroplast") | is.na(Class))
ntaxa(po)
## [1] 2205
po = phyloseq::subset_taxa(po, (Family!="mitochondria") | is.na(Family))
ntaxa(po)
## [1] 2205


First pass quality control check of all samples with negative controls

pcoa = phyloseq::ordinate(po, method="PCoA", distance="bray")

(plot_ordination(po, pcoa) +
    geom_point(aes(fill=Timepoint, shape=Sample_Type), size=3) +
    scale_fill_manual(values = c("green4", "mediumorchid4", "indianred", "steelblue", "yellow", "orange"), na.value = "darkgrey") +
    scale_shape_manual(values = c(22, 23, 24, 25, 21), name="Sample Type") +                            
    theme_linedraw(14) +
    guides(fill = guide_legend(override.aes=list(shape=21))) + #required due to bug in manually setting shape; https://github.com/tidyverse/ggplot2/issues/2322
    guides(shape = guide_legend(override.aes=list(size=3))) +
    theme(panel.grid=element_blank())
)

ggsave("figures_unfiltered/allsamples_ordination_bray.png", width=10, height=8)
observed = phyloseq::estimate_richness(po, measures=c("Observed")) 
observed$Sample_ID=row.names(observed)
observed$Sample_ID=gsub("\\.", "-", observed$Sample_ID) #fix dashes that phyloseq converted to periods

richness = observed %>%
    left_join(sampledata, by="Sample_ID") 

richness = richness %>%
  arrange(Sample_Type, Specimen, Timepoint) %>%
  mutate(Timepoint = coalesce(as.character(Timepoint), as.character(Sample_Type))) %>% #fill NA w Sample_Type in Timepoint for ctrls w no Timepoint
  mutate(Timepoint = factor(Timepoint, levels = c("NTC", "CTRL_NEG","CTRL_Zymo","CTRL_Human", "Pre-Sm", "Post-Sm (Pre-Col)", "Post-Col", "T0", "T1", "T2"))) %>%
  mutate(order=Sample_ID) %>%
  mutate(order=factor(order, levels=order)) 
p1=ggplot(richness) +
  geom_bar(aes(x=order, y=Observed, fill=Timepoint), stat="identity", width=1, colour="black", size=0.35) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") +
  scale_x_discrete(name="\nSample") +
  scale_y_continuous(name="Observed SVs\n", expand=c(0,0)) +
  theme_linedraw(12) +
  theme(panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(), axis.text.x = element_blank(), axis.ticks=element_blank(), 
        plot.margin=unit(c(1.5,0.5,0.5,0.5),"cm"))
p2=ggplot(richness) +
    geom_bar(aes(x=order, y=Reads, fill=Timepoint), stat="identity", width=1, colour="black", size=0.35) +
    scale_fill_brewer(palette = "Set1") +
    geom_hline(yintercept = max, linetype="dashed", colour="black", size=0.25) +
    theme_linedraw(12) +
    scale_y_continuous(name="Reads in fastq file\n", labels=scales::comma, expand=c(0,0)) +
    scale_x_discrete(name="\nSample") +
    theme(panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(), axis.text.x = element_blank(), axis.ticks=element_blank(), 
          plot.margin=unit(c(1.5,0.5,0.5,0.5),"cm"))
pdf(NULL)
combined=ggarrange(p2, p1, align='v', common.legend = T, nrow=2, legend="right")
x=dev.off()

Examine the controls

controls = filter(richness, Sample_Type != "Mouse")
rownames(controls) = controls$Sample_ID

po_controls = prune_samples(controls$Sample_ID, po)
sample_data(po_controls) = controls

pcoa = phyloseq::ordinate(po_controls, method="PCoA", distance="bray")

controls = tibble(Sample_ID = rownames(pcoa$vectors), 
                 Axis1 = pcoa$vectors[,"Axis.1"], 
                 Axis2 =  pcoa$vectors[,"Axis.2"], 
                 Relative_EigenValue1 = pcoa$values[,"Relative_eig"][1],
                 Relative_EigenValue2 = pcoa$values[,"Relative_eig"][2]) %>%
  left_join(richness, by="Sample_ID") %>%
  mutate(NumSVs_NumReads = paste0(Observed, " (", Reads, ")")) 
set.seed(1000)
RelativeEig1 = controls$Relative_EigenValue1[1] * 100
RelativeEig2 = controls$Relative_EigenValue2[1] * 100

(ggplot(controls, aes(x=Axis1, y=Axis2)) +
    geom_text(aes(colour=Sample_Type, label=NumSVs_NumReads, fontface = "bold"), 
              position=position_jitter(height=0.1, width=0.1), size=2.5) +
    scale_x_continuous(name=paste0("\nBray Axis 1  [", round(RelativeEig1), "%]"), limits=c(-0.5, 0.5)) +
    scale_y_continuous(name=paste0("\nBray Axis 2  [", round(RelativeEig2), "%]")) +
    scale_colour_brewer(palette = "Dark2") +
    theme_linedraw(14) +
    theme(panel.grid=element_blank())
)

ggsave("figures_unfiltered/controls_ordination_bray.png", width=10, height=8)


Compare diversity pre- and post- streptomycin treatment

observed = phyloseq::estimate_richness(po, measures=c("Observed")) 
observed$Sample_ID=row.names(observed)
observed$Sample_ID=gsub("\\.", "-", observed$Sample_ID) #fix dashes that phyloseq converted to periods

richness = observed %>%
    inner_join(sampledata, observed, by="Sample_ID")

richness = richness %>%
    arrange(Sample_Type, Specimen, Timepoint) %>%
    mutate(Timepoint = coalesce(as.character(Timepoint), as.character(Sample_Type))) %>% #fill NA w Sample_Type in Timepoint for ctrls w no Timepoint
    filter(Timepoint != "Post-Col" & Timepoint != "T0" & Timepoint != "T1" & Timepoint != "T2") %>%
    filter(Sample_Type == "Mouse" | Sample_Type == "NTC" | Sample_Type == "CTRL_NEG") %>%
    mutate(Timepoint = gsub("NTC", "No Template Ctrl", Timepoint)) %>%
    mutate(Timepoint = gsub("CTRL_NEG", "DNA Extraction Ctrl", Timepoint)) 
  
#save Sample_IDs for all samples
sample_list_all = richness %>%
    pull(Sample_ID)

#save Sample_IDs for mice only
sample_list_mice = richness %>%
    filter(Sample_Type =="Mouse") %>% 
    pull(Sample_ID)
po_subset = prune_samples(sample_list_all, po)
sample_data(po_subset) = richness %>% column_to_rownames("Sample_ID")

pcoa = ordinate(po_subset, method="PCoA", distance="bray")

p1s=phyloseq::plot_ordination(po_subset, pcoa) +
    geom_point(aes(fill=Timepoint), size=4, shape=21, stroke=0.75) +
    scale_x_continuous(limits=c(-0.5, 0.5)) +
    scale_y_continuous(limits=c(-0.7, 0.4)) +
    scale_fill_manual(values=c("grey70", "grey30", "mediumorchid4", "green4")) +
    theme_linedraw(14) +
    theme(panel.grid = element_blank(), 
          panel.border = element_rect(size=1.25),
          panel.background = element_rect(colour="black", size=1), 
          legend.title=element_blank()) 
#order the specimens by rank number of observed Pre-Sm
mouse_order = richness %>%
    filter(Timepoint=="Pre-Sm") %>%
    arrange(desc(Observed)) %>%
    pull(Specimen)

richness_mice = richness %>%
    group_by(Timepoint) %>%
    mutate(order=Specimen) %>%
    mutate(order=factor(order, levels=mouse_order)) %>%
    ungroup() %>%
    filter(Sample_Type == "Mouse") %>%
    mutate(Timepoint = factor(Timepoint, levels=c("Pre-Sm","Post-Sm (Pre-Col)")))

p2s=ggplot(richness_mice) +
  geom_bar(aes(x=order, y=Observed, fill=Timepoint), stat="identity", position="dodge", width=0.75, colour="black", size=0.5) +
  scale_x_discrete(name="Mouse") +
  scale_y_continuous(name="Observed SVs", expand=c(0,0), limits=c(0,550)) +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("green4", "mediumorchid4")) +
  theme_linedraw(14) +
  theme(panel.grid = element_blank(), 
        panel.border = element_rect(size=1.25),
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90, hjust=1),
        legend.title=element_blank(),
        panel.background = element_rect(colour="black", size=1))
set.seed(22)
p3s=ggplot(richness_mice, aes(x=Timepoint, y=Observed, group=Timepoint, colour=Timepoint, fill=Timepoint)) +
  geom_bar(stat="summary", fun=mean, position="dodge", width=0.65, colour="black", size=0.65) +
  geom_text(stat="summary", fun=mean, aes(label=round(..y..), vjust = -10, fontface="bold"), show.legend=FALSE) +        
  geom_jitter(shape=21, width=0.2, height=15, size=2.5, fill="white", stroke=0.75, colour="black") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("green4", "mediumorchid4")) +
  scale_colour_manual(values = c("darkgreen", "purple4")) +
  scale_x_discrete(name="Timepoint") +
  scale_y_continuous(name="", expand=c(0,0), limits=c(0,550)) +
  theme_linedraw(14) +
  theme(panel.grid = element_blank(), 
        panel.border = element_rect(size=1.25),
        axis.text.x = element_text(angle=0),
        legend.title = element_blank(), 
        panel.background = element_rect(colour="black", size=1))
pdf(NULL) #hack fix for blank page problem w common legend; https://github.com/kassambara/ggpubr/issues/158
combined = ggpubr::ggarrange(p1s + theme(axis.title.x = element_text(vjust=0)), 
                             
                             ggarrange(p2s + theme(axis.title.x = element_text(vjust=0)), 
                                       p3s + theme(axis.title.x = element_text(vjust=0)),
                                       align="h", nrow=1, common.legend = TRUE, legend="right", widths=c(3,1), labels=c("b","c")), 
                             
                             nrow=2, heights=c(6, 5), labels="a")
x=dev.off()
combined
